## Dval ##

Dval (short form of Dvalarr) is a basement for modular java applications. It provides module managment and other helpful features and utilities.

Current features are:

  - application locking (start only one instance)
  - exithook (write log after crash, etc)
  - logging
  - module loading

Current utilities are:

  - Config (useful for loading setting-files, like Properites)
  - Version (comparing module versions)
  - easy text file reading and value parsing
  - some other

# Note #

Version 0.10.0 was developed for a specific project and will not supported. As of version 0.11.0 Dval will be feature-complete.
